##New Year's Eve dinner in Wuhan: Never so simple, never so important

New-weekly

Function Introduction "new weekly" was first published on August 18,1996, and was sponsored by Southern Publishing Media Co. , Ltd. . With the orientation of "China's newest and cutting-edge lifestyle weekly" , it published a series of special reports with great influence, it is one of the most representative and influential magazines in China's periodical market, and enjoys the reputation of "topic source" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This year's New Year's Eve is special for the people of Wuhan and even for the people of the whole country. Eat Drink Man Woman

Yesterday, I posted a friend circle, asked Wuhan friends how to eat New Year's Eve dinner, all the responses are: canceled all the New Year's Eve dinner and party.

The day before New Year's Eve, more than ten in the morning, aunt in the family wechat group sent a message: "Cancel New Year's Eve dinner, please understand. "

It was a late decision, but it was timely. By then, Wuhan had officially been "closed, " the city's public transport shutdown, the airport, railway station from the Han channel has been closed.

Before this, a lot of my friends in Wuhan didn't take this outbreak seriously. Friends Circle, can see a lot of their self-deprecating joke, "the whole world thinks something happened in Wuhan, only Wuhan people are thinking about where to go tonight. "

Behind this, in addition to the huge Information asymmetry, is the breaking of most people's Conventional Wisdom: An epidemic that lasts more than 20 days and then suddenly gets out of control.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The empty streets of Wuhan after the city's closure. /@lin Chen Hearing

The result was unexpected. My cousin, who had come back from Singapore to Wuhan for the New Year, had seen the signs earlier. Her return ticket was rescheduled a week earlier, but she still didn't expect to be detained. After the holiday, she would send an email to the school to explain the situation.

As it turns out, the school has been on this for quite some time -- as if half a month ago, every student filled out a questionnaire asking them to keep a record of anyone who had been to China in the last three months.

Unfortunately, an epidemic is likely to spread faster than people's alertness. Ordinary people are unprepared for this.

On Monday, I told my mother that I couldn't go home this year and would return my ticket back to Wuhan. Mom was a little puzzled, she asked me: prepared a lot of your favorite things, how can not go home New Year?

Before that day, there was a feast for over 40,000 people at the Baibu pavilion in Hankou. I am also in the family group, optimistic to say: "Out of security considerations, I do not go home for the New Year. Mainly airports, high-speed railway stations, closed space has the risk of infection. There should be nothing in the urban area. "

We live in Wuchang, across the Yangtze River from the South China Seafood Market. Every day, I keep up with the latest news, but until a few days ago, I didn't think my family was in danger.

Until yesterday, I didn't know there were fewer than ten masks in the house. Because GRANDPA died last year, although the cancellation of the New Year's Eve dinner, but the father insisted on holding the incense ceremony at home as scheduled.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The New Year's Eve dinner is of great significance to the Chinese. Eat Drink Man Woman

Today after the New Year's Eve, according to the custom, the door of the home will be opened to welcome the relatives and friends who come to the door. In this case, most people probably won't come, but it's hard to predict who will.

My father didn't care much about the epidemic, and many of his drinking friends and former comrades were as opinionated as he was.

You don't have to call before this visit. My cousin, who lives in my home, sent me a message on Wechat: "Your father went out to buy sugar. "

Mother and sister, aware of some danger, but also some unaware. They had not yet decided whether they should refuse visitors who did not wear masks?

This year, my family does not have New Year's Eve dinner

In Wuhan, I always feel very cold and cheerless. My mother was not from here, and my grandfather was a foreigner. At 1950s, my grandfather borrowed the identity and academic credentials of his fellow villagers, left his family in Hebei Province and enrolled in a state run factory in Wuhan.

I still don't know his real name or his exact age. He died of illness last May, in his nineties.

I have never eaten more than one New Year's dinner, and my relatives on the other side of the border -- Florida -- are her three sons (including my father) , her brother (my father) , and his two daughters (my aunt) . Besides, I have three cousins and two cousins. Every year on the twenty-eight th day of the lunar calendar, on my grandfather's birthday, we all have dinner together.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The family celebrated GRANDPA's birthday

When I was a kid, all six kids ate at a small table. Over the past decade, we have grown up, the marriage of two cousins, relatives of the warm feelings between the many dilute.

My father's generation, including my aunt, was brought up by my grandmother, who worked in a yarn factory. She often told them to support each other. When they grew up, most of them went to work in a car factory in Wuchang.

In our generation, we all have different ideas, different occupations, the relationship has long been off. After grandma died, the brothers moved less. It used to be that the big family was, naturally, a different little family.

Therefore, it is very important for us to have a New Year's Eve dinner together in the new year to maintain a sense of intimacy that is no longer apparent.

In the first year after GRANDPA's death, it is customary for the family to be reunited. This could have been our last reunion dinner, we have a tacit understanding with each other, do not have to force together New Year's Eve.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Although the taste of the year gradually faded, but this year especially want to get together with family reunion dinner. Don't tell her

In the eight years since grandma died, the whole family has been able to eat together, in addition to aunt hard, and mother has been willing to pay. Every time, the New Year's Eve dinner is held in my home, my mother to prepare to do about twenty people's food.

A large family at the dinner table, while eating vegetables while watching the Spring Festival gala, the mother is still in the kitchen stir-fry, side dishes, hot dishes. We have never had dinner in a hotel, more than 10 years ago, I thought it was too expensive, and then I worried that my relatives would be too rude.

This time, aunt as usual to buy more than 10 pounds of fish, pork, fried meatballs at home. Wuhan, Fried meatballs is a must-have dish for New Year's Eve dinner. It's weird. It's so good when it comes out of the Pan, but then it goes flat. These meatballs will be frozen in the refrigerator in advance of the new year to eat.

When the meatballs are ready, the aunt will ride the scooter and give them to her brothers. Every time we received meatballs, sausage, and Bacon from our aunt, we knew that the new year was not far off.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The women in the family are the main force of the New Year's Eve dinner. Don't tell her

The arrival of the epidemic, these days it is difficult to buy food, aunt's meatballs just became a backup food. Because of the epidemic, just canceled my family has been some awkward New Year's Eve dinner.

In recent years, the family has long been accustomed to the new year, no firecrackers outside the window, after dinner, we go home to watch TV. This time only left the empty living room, mother continued to tie the Apron, tidy up the table, New Year's eve is thus over.

"information is published online,

The old man has no idea what's going on."

On the morning of the closing of the city, my mother went to the market to make the final preparations for the New Year dinner tomorrow. But she didn't get much more than two cabbages. "The market was empty, " she said, estimating that the family had enough food to last a week. "A lot of people came in early in the morning. ".

New Information from the family group advised against going to the supermarket to snap up more. Crowded places may become new places of infection. On weekdays, relatives rely on "family wechat group" contact, which has 21 people. Few people speak, occasionally a few elders, retweeting some "popular science" , "inspirational" short essays.

At the beginning of the month, I turned a few "new pneumonia" news to the group, few people replied. Until after January 20, the family wechat group information has become more and more, heated discussion of the response measures. They also post small videos, such as "xxxx people have been quarantined, people do not go out. "

We're taking this more and more seriously. In recent days, my mother went to a nearby three-fly vegetable market, where a vegetable vendor was quarantined after a few days of fever. There was also a suspected sick man in a neighborhood near my aunt's house.

"I know that surgical masks can only be worn for four hours, " my aunt told me over the phone. "When you're done, put it in a garbage bag and tie it off to avoid secondary contamination. ".

Not all middle-aged and elderly people do not wear masks, do not form such stereotypes. / Graphic design

In 1985, she worked in Xujiapeng Street, during more than a decade when the Director of the Neighborhood Committee, worked until retirement.

In 2003, when SARS was spreading, she was in charge of neighborhood searches. "At that time, we had to go door-to-door and register neighborhoods that had come back from abroad. Wuhan is not a hard-hit area, and the atmosphere is not as tense as it is now. "

After calling my aunt, she left me a message on Wechat:

"Seal a city, love a nation, and pray for the health and safety of all. In 1998, I worked in the street office and the Civil Affairs Office, and participated in the flood relief work. Worked in the community, won two honors as a community worker in Wuhan. Your aunt is a hard worker."

But not everyone feels the same way. Chinese cabbage sold for more than 30 catties.

In fact, each region supply volume is different, the rise is not the same situation. On the day of the siege, a friend prepared even earlier, and from 1 a.m. to 7 a.m. , she managed to fill the fridge.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Knowing the severity of pneumonia, many Wuhan residents began to stock up on grain. /@lin Chen Hearing

"The information was posted on the Internet. The poor old man didn't know what happened. Many old people complained about the high price of food when they went shopping this morning. They left in disgust. "

In my family, my father rarely read wechat group content, he is also the most do not care about the epidemic. He did not want to wear a mask in public before his family tried to persuade him to do so.

Every day, there were new changes in the epidemic, but the father insisted on the tradition: at home, as scheduled, GRANDPA's incense ceremony.

When they realized they needed to buy more masks,

There aren't many places to buy it anymore

Today's incense, in addition to the father, the whole family seems to be a little worried. We can not predict how many people will come to visit US after New Year's Eve.

Aunt out of the plan, "out of courtesy, can not refuse to come to the incense guests. We have to wear masks, followed by people say sorry, incense can not serve you. "

But at the end of the day, in my father's house, he's the boss. Yesterday, he went to buy some candy for those who stayed.

In the WECHAT group, I said to the guests, hand out masks. My cousin replied that there weren't that many masks in the house. I didn't think. I didn't ask.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the face of pneumonia, we must not take it lightly. We must wear a mask. / unsplash

My father was a very quiet and stubborn man. He was a little upset about the cancellation of the New Year's Eve dinner.

As the eldest son, he rarely pay attention to relatives, but he did not want the past big family, because the death of parents "so scattered. ". He also wants us to respect our guests. In the telephone, he has some impatiently, "the other person stays, can not not not entertain to eat? "

I called my family yesterday and found out that they were in dire need of supplies. There are only 30 surgical masks in my aunt's house, 50 in my cousin's house, and less than 10 in mine.

This number, can not cope with the new year a few days of visitors. A few days ago, my mother also replied to me in Wechat, "enough. ".

Doctors and nurses on the front lines fighting pneumonia also need masks. /@2020 CCTV gala

My mother was more concerned about my new year's resolutions than the current outbreak, wechat repeatedly asked me: "The new year alone, will not be too boring? " "You can early return to Beijing, I and a friend agreed, can go to her home for the New Year. " "outside to take care of themselves. "

My cousin told me, "Tuesday can still buy masks at the drugstore, and they were all sold out the next day. " I asked around and found that many of my friends were in short supply. In recent days, when they realized they needed to buy more masks, there weren't many places to buy them.

Hearing about the shortage of face masks at home, I felt some remorse. As early as December 31, I turned to the news group of "pneumonia" and sent out several links to buy face masks.

The rest of the time, I spent a lot of time every day, to keep up with the latest developments, constantly in the circle of friends screen. On wechat, I told my elders many times to wear masks, but I forgot to buy masks for them in person.

These days, people in the field I have been very anxious, frequently brush the mobile phone information. In the hotel bed, I do not want to get up for a long time, once dreamed that we eat together, grandpa sitting next to me. He looked at me with a smile and asked me to pour a drink (he doesn't like his grandson to drink) .

When I woke up, I felt a little sad. It was a sunny day in the seaside city as if nothing had happened. It was lunar twenty-nine, my grandfather's birthday.

Last night, I ordered several masks, but a few minutes later I got a return message from the store. Just this one -- a total of 30 surgical masks, plus a delivery fee of over $200, delivered the next day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I wasn't expecting much, but at nine o'clock this morning, I turned on the delivery platform software, and the map said "rider is delivering" .

Mom told me she got the mask. She sent a picture of two pots of washed garlic moss and peas. She was preparing lunch.

No matter how hard it is, the New Year will pass

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I was a little relieved that, in the worst case scenario, my family would have a tough new year ahead of the arrival of more than 100 surgical masks purchased online.

I hope that more supplies can be delivered to Wuhan. I hope that parents, family members, friends and everyone in Wuhan, including those in other places affected by the epidemic, will be safe and sound. I hope that during the New Year, we have more patience than I communicate with the elderly, as far as possible to cancel the party.

We've got a lot of good new year's Eve left after this outbreak.

Reporter's notes

I'm Zhao Jingyi, Beijing correspondent for new weekly. This year, I did not go home to Wuhan New Year.

In this week of rapid development of the "epidemic" , many friends and relatives of Wuhan in a state of confusion.

I wish this would all go away. I hope during the New Year, we have more patience than I communicate with the elderly, as far as possible to cancel the party dinner. Peace, after all, is what makes it last.

By Zhao Jingyi
